Small, fine billed warbler with all green above, white to slight yellow tinged underside. White undertail coverts and faint wing bars. Dark eye stripe and pale supercilium. Closely associating with a grey headed OCWA. Mostly heard giving its sharp double up-slur flight call. Similar to OCWA but sounds shorter and sharper in the field. Occasionally giving its chip note.
 Spending most of the time in the willows around the secret pond area.
